==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''paides'', '''boy''' + ''erasteio'', '''to ''long'' for.'''

===Noun===
'''pederasty''' (''uncountable'')

#Erotic love between a man and an adolescent boy. 

====Usage note====
Originally referred to formal practices mandated by Greek laws. Often used in a modern sense for transgressive inter-generational love relationships.

